  "text": "where ϕunexposed and ϕexposed were reflected intensities of light from the unexposed and exposed film to UV radiation, respectively. The experimental Net ROD was defined as Net ROD = log(Pu/Pt), where Pu and Pt were the pixel values of the reflected intensities through an unexposed film and an exposed film, respectively. Here, the UV exposure values were taken from previous work by Chun et al. [CITATION_1] .",
